{
  "texts": [
    "While we have implemented certain measures to reduce the risk of misinterpretation as outlined in the methodology section, we acknowledge that the potential for misinterpretation cannot be entirely eliminated.",
    "Future work could incorporate approaches such as engagement with primary data sources (e.g., interviews with the authors of included articles or practitioners involved in implementing RAI practices), including grey literature to help triangulate findings from peer-reviewed articles, conducting validation, interdisciplinary workshops with experts to refine interpretation of, for example, RAI practices, lifecycle phase, levels of risks, and roles of AI-enabled systems.",
    "Combining several research methods, such as SLR with observational studies or fieldwork in real-world settings may also allow researchers to calibrate interpretations across these elements.Fourth, our review does not document evidence of the impact of the suggested RAI practices.",
    "This is because none of the included articles focused on measuring the impact, there is very little documented or reported evidence of the suggested RAI practices, and most of the data is in the form of descriptions of real-world stakeholder or expert suggestions of how RAI is supposed or expected to be practiced, perceptions of the development or deployment process of AI-enabled systems, or evaluation of AI-enabled systems.",
    "Future work should thus focus on exploring methods to the perceptions of RAI practices are likely to be different among primary, user, and non-user stakeholders within settings where an AI-enabled system is (to be) deployed [71], and thus their different perceptions should be captured to provide a more complete picture of RAI."
  ]
}